it should be fine.

897
00:38:13,140 --> 00:38:14,100
Are you sure?

898
00:38:14,820 --> 00:38:16,660
She's an old lady in her sixties.

899
00:38:17,380 --> 00:38:19,460
She did business

900
00:38:20,100 --> 00:38:21,380
in the '80s or '90s.

901
00:38:21,820 --> 00:38:23,620
She didn't have computers

902
00:38:23,780 --> 00:38:24,940
or printers.

903
00:38:30,620 --> 00:38:31,330
Right.

904
00:38:40,980 --> 00:38:41,940
Aunt Wu,

905
00:38:42,580 --> 00:38:44,180
are you kidding me?

906
00:38:44,420 --> 00:38:45,610
I asked you to print things.

907
00:38:45,740 --> 00:38:48,420
Did you drop these in the ink box?

908
00:38:49,980 --> 00:38:52,100
I don't know what's wrong with the machine.

909
00:38:52,580 --> 00:38:54,260
Well, I...

910
00:38:54,380 --> 00:38:56,780
I'll ask someone to take a look.

911
00:38:56,900 --> 00:38:57,540
Okay.

912
00:38:57,620 --> 00:38:59,060
You're not familiar with the machine, fine.

913
00:38:59,180 --> 00:39:00,340
What about these?

914
00:39:00,580 --> 00:39:01,980
I said color printing.

915
00:39:02,020 --> 00:39:03,580
Why are they all black and white?

916
00:39:05,780 --> 00:39:07,820
Fine, I can forget about all of these.

917
00:39:07,980 --> 00:39:09,060
What about the report?

918
00:39:09,460 --> 00:39:10,940
Why haven't you given it to me?

919
00:39:11,140 --> 00:39:12,380
I've sent you the template.

920
00:39:12,460 --> 00:39:13,180
How much have you done?

921
00:39:13,340 --> 00:39:14,660
Can you give it to me today?

922
00:39:15,740 --> 00:39:16,540
Sorry.

923
00:39:16,620 --> 00:39:18,580
The computer, I…

924
00:39:18,740 --> 00:39:19,820
I don't know how to use it yet.

925
00:39:20,020 --> 00:39:21,780
I’m working on the software.

926
00:39:22,260 --> 00:39:24,340
I'll write one.

927
00:39:24,500 --> 00:39:26,060
I can write one.

928
00:39:26,140 --> 00:39:27,980
A handwritten form is useless to me.

929
00:39:28,100 --> 00:39:29,540
I need it for my PowerPoint.

930
00:39:29,820 --> 00:39:31,540
Am I supposed to take a photo of it?

931
00:39:32,380 --> 00:39:33,620
You can.

932
00:39:35,900 --> 00:39:37,620
Okay, it's done.

933
00:39:40,450 --> 00:39:41,940
Thank you for your hard work.

934
00:39:42,060 --> 00:39:43,540
It's the efforts of everyone of our team

935
00:39:43,660 --> 00:39:45,900
that leads to the completion of the preliminary plan.

936
00:39:45,980 --> 00:39:46,780
Go home tonight

937
00:39:46,860 --> 00:39:47,740
and have a good sleep.

938
00:39:47,820 --> 00:39:48,660
Tomorrow we'll gather our energy

939
00:39:48,780 --> 00:39:49,620
and check the plan.

940
00:39:49,740 --> 00:39:51,980
Hu Dexiang is really good.

941
00:39:52,060 --> 00:39:53,260
Of course.

942
00:39:53,460 --> 00:39:55,740
She has a lot of people working for her.

943
00:39:55,980 --> 00:39:57,260
There's no other

944
00:39:57,380 --> 00:39:59,420
chief designer like her in the company.

945
00:39:59,660 --> 00:40:00,620
I think she'll win

946
00:40:00,740 --> 00:40:01,780
this case.

947
00:40:04,020 --> 00:40:05,450
Obviously.

948
00:40:06,290 --> 00:40:07,460
The rumor about her promotion

949
00:40:07,500 --> 00:40:09,060
at the end of the year may be true.

950
00:40:09,420 --> 00:40:11,660
She's on fire.

951
00:40:13,060 --> 00:40:14,460
They are fast.

952
00:40:14,780 --> 00:40:15,380
Sorry, Aunt Wu.

953
00:40:15,460 --> 00:40:16,300
I was just anxious.

954
00:40:16,420 --> 00:40:17,660
I didn't mean what I said.

955
00:40:18,100 --> 00:40:19,460
You go fix the printer.

956
00:40:19,620 --> 00:40:20,980
I’ll make the report forms myself.

957
00:40:22,890 --> 00:40:23,460
Jiang.

958
00:40:23,580 --> 00:40:25,180
Stop talking. Hurry up.

959
00:40:25,580 --> 00:40:27,020
We’re really late.

960
00:40:56,740 --> 00:40:58,660
Jiang, slow down.

961
00:40:58,820 --> 00:40:59,940
Why are you walking so fast?

962
00:41:00,020 --> 00:41:01,660
I can't keep up.

963
00:41:02,340 --> 00:41:03,980
I still have a lot of work to do.

964
00:41:04,260 --> 00:41:05,580
I have to finish the drawing tonight

965
00:41:05,580 --> 00:41:06,900
so that we can check it tomorrow.

966
00:41:08,180 --> 00:41:09,820
What can I do for you?

967
00:41:10,420 --> 00:41:12,020
Really, I can help you.

968
00:41:14,980 --> 00:41:15,980
What took you so long?

969
00:41:16,020 --> 00:41:17,260
My mom has been looking for you.

970
00:41:17,900 --> 00:41:18,770
Oh no.

971
00:41:19,300 --> 00:41:20,340
Today is her birthday.

972
00:41:20,500 --> 00:41:21,260
My phone is dead.

973
00:41:21,420 --> 00:41:22,540
Come on! Give me your phone.

974
00:41:22,860 --> 00:41:24,340
I'll video call her.

975
00:41:26,340 --> 00:41:29,060
Don't be angry, sis.

976
00:41:29,420 --> 00:41:31,260
Anger gives you wrinkles.

977
00:41:31,460 --> 00:41:32,460
I'll sing for you.

978
00:41:34,180 --> 00:41:37,050
Happy birthday to you!

979
00:41:37,300 --> 00:41:40,260
Happy birthday to you!

980
00:41:40,460 --> 00:41:44,500
Happy birthday to you!

981
00:41:44,980 --> 00:41:48,740
Happy birthday to you!

982
00:41:48,860 --> 00:41:50,780
Happy birthday!

983
00:41:52,420 --> 00:41:53,780
That's enough.

984
00:41:53,980 --> 00:41:55,580
You only care about your work.

985
00:41:55,940 --> 00:41:57,420
You completely forgot about me, didn't you?

986
00:41:57,940 --> 00:41:58,860
No.

987
00:41:58,940 --> 00:42:01,020
My phone died.

988
00:42:01,900 --> 00:42:02,860
I bought you a gift.

989
00:42:02,980 --> 00:42:04,060
I'm sure you'll like it.

990
00:42:04,260 --> 00:42:05,940
I'll ask Wen to send it to you later.

991
00:42:06,780 --> 00:42:07,820
Stop it.

992
00:42:08,180 --> 00:42:10,140
You taking good care of yourself

993
00:42:10,380 --> 00:42:12,100
is the biggest gift to me, you know?

994
00:42:12,500 --> 00:42:13,420
How are you?

995
00:42:13,580 --> 00:42:14,580
Are you tired?

996
00:42:15,860 --> 00:42:17,060
You're over 60.

997
00:42:17,260 --> 00:42:19,020
Don't push yourself too hard.

998
00:42:19,100 --> 00:42:20,580
Don't overwork.

999
00:42:21,060 --> 00:42:23,140
Don't worry. I'm doing great.

1000
00:42:23,300 --> 00:42:24,540
See? I'm doing great.

1001
00:42:30,140 --> 00:42:31,180
My aunt is old.

1002
00:42:31,300 --> 00:42:32,660
She doesn't have to work overtime until this hour.

1003
00:42:34,780 --> 00:42:35,980
What does it have to do with you?

1004
00:42:35,980 --> 00:42:36,900
She is my aunt.

1005
00:42:37,020 --> 00:42:38,820
Your aunt chose to work,

1006
00:42:38,940 --> 00:42:39,660
she has to

1007
00:42:39,780 --> 00:42:41,100
take on the responsibilities.

1008
00:42:41,500 --> 00:42:43,500
All kinds of jobs require overtime nowadays.

1009
00:42:43,900 --> 00:42:45,260
I didn't force her.

1010
00:42:45,500 --> 00:42:47,020
She chose all this.

1011
00:42:47,580 --> 00:42:48,740
You can tell her that.

1012
00:42:48,900 --> 00:42:49,740
You can't blame me for

1013
00:42:49,820 --> 00:42:51,010
her wearing herself out.

1014
00:42:51,260 --> 00:42:52,860
Besides, she's your aunt, so what?

1015
00:42:52,980 --> 00:42:54,300
Everyone is independent.

1016
00:42:54,820 --> 00:42:55,980
She didn't say anything.

1017
00:42:56,540 --> 00:42:58,380
You're just being nosy.

1018
00:42:58,460 --> 00:42:59,820
Don't make a fuss over her.

1019
00:43:03,900 --> 00:43:05,460
She's on fire.

